# What file contains the RSA keys of systems that are authorized to connect via SSH?
~/.ssh/authorized_keys
# RSA is a private key used for authentication +  secure data transmission
# the encription key is public and the decription key is kept secret (private)
#ssh-keygen -t rsa
# The known_hosts file lets the client authenticate the server, to check that it isn't connecting to an impersonator. 
# The authorized_keys file lets the server authenticate the user.